From: Hariprasad Shenai <hariprasad@chelsio.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2015 02:02:30 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 223/230] cxgb4: Increased the value of MAX_IMM_TX_PKT_LEN from
 128 to 256 bytes
Patch-mainline: v4.1-rc1
Git-commit: 21dcfad6401b008e7352eb95104c7f199f025ac9
References: bsc#924378 FATE#318565 bsc#921338

This allows a significant latency drop for packets of sizes between 128 and 192
bytes

Signed-off-by: Hariprasad Shenai <hariprasad@chelsio.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: David Chang <dchang@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/chelsio/cxgb4/sge.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/chelsio/cxgb4/sge.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/chelsio/cxgb4/sge.c
@@ -144,7 +144,7 @@
  * Max Tx descriptor space we allow for an Ethernet packet to be inlined
  * into a WR.
  */
-#define MAX_IMM_TX_PKT_LEN 128
+#define MAX_IMM_TX_PKT_LEN 256
 
 /*
  * Max size of a WR sent through a control Tx queue.
